{[show NESW]
[ROLE leader][STAGE pre-lead]
Lead the \HK from your long, strong suit — top of the sequence, the textbook notrump lead.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE auction-end]
Dummy's \DA\DK\DQ\DJ give you four tricks on their own, and two finesses supply the rest: a spade finesse and a club finesse, both of which lose only to East. West's hearts are the threat, so duck a round to protect yourself, then run your diamonds and take both finesses into the safe East hand.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-lead]
Duck the opening heart — East had three, so hold up until the third round leaves him with none. Cash dummy's diamonds, then take the club finesse and the spade finesse; both lose to East, who is now heartless and cannot put West on lead. Combining the two chances brings home ten tricks.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-play]
With the danger hand shut out by the hold-up, the two finesses were pure profit — a loss on either simply went to the safe hand. Counting your tricks and knowing which loser you can afford is what turns a close game into a comfortable one.}
